{"type":"text","timestamp":1784851331427,"sessionID":"ses_06e92a00affej0iMHtj8Hsslfy","part":{"id":"prt_f916df13f001b6j8sQABK8yOfW","messageID":"msg_f916debf0001R7E6nz7KJO2veq","sessionID":"ses_06e92a00affej0iMHtj8Hsslfy","type":"text","text":"Implemented core backend enhancements for EchoPlex:\n\n- **Thread‑safety fix** – Replaced incorrect `events_lock` references with the correct `_events_lock`.\n- **Optional spaCy integration** – Added safe import and model loading; falls back gracefully if unavailable.\n- **Embedding‑based pattern detection** – Extended `_simple_pattern_engine` to compute cosine similarity between event embeddings (threshold > 0.8) and include results as a new pattern.\n- **List all events endpoint** – `GET /events` returns the full in‑memory event collection.\n- **Improved documentation strings** and added logging for spaCy load failures.\n- **Minor code clean‑up** – Updated imports and added explanatory comments.\n\nThese changes move the project beyond placeholder logic, providing a functional ingestion pipeline, richer pattern detection using NLP embeddings, and a basic API to explore stored events. The backend now runs without the previous `NameError` and is ready for further integration with PostgreSQL, Neo4j, and the frontend UI.","time":{"start":1784851329343,"end":1784851331423}}}
